#purgatory_hospital_nurse
	Stop!
	You have ink fever.
	There is no known cure for this illness and the outcome is certain.
	Initially, the virus strips you of your dignity.
	Then it takes away individuality and personality.
	In the end you will you will die a horrible death.
	Alone, forgotten, scared and confused.
	A fate so terrible that most people decide to take desperate measures.
	Initially, we helped the infected cross to the "other side".
	But their numbers were too large.
	The poison bottles have dried up.
	The blades have become dull.
	Then the sick resorted to more drastic measures.
	People were banging their heads against the sharp corners.
	But their sticky, inky blood covered the walls...
	Cushioned them.
	Making getting hurt harder and harder...
	So... Patients found other desperate methods.
	Some people started pulling nails out of the boards.
	One person ate so much garbage that he couldn't breathe.
	Everything is better than the brutal, slow death caused by ink.
	Unfortunately, you showed up here very late.
	I'm powerless, and I cannot help you.
	You have to find your own way to wake up.
#purgatory_hospital_nurse_02
	At first we used this hole to throw away bodies.
	Too many infected, too little time and hands for a proper burial.
	However, over time people became desperate.
	They couldn't crack their heads open on the doorframe... so they started jumping into this hole, hoping to die.
	There are a lot of bodies down there.
	Corpses cushion the fall...
	They made the landing safe.
	That's why we covered this hole.
	There was no reason for people to spend their final moments lying on a pile of corpses.
	Now the moans have subsided.
	We are the last ones left here.
	I couldn't help these people.
	I couldn't give them a proper burial.
	But I can join them.
	"Death here is life there."
	I can only wish to wake up rested one day...
